        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> type alias\r\n\r\n[`TypeAlias`](https://docs.python.org/3/library/typing.html#typing.TypeAlias) was only added in Python 3.10, and is already deprecated in Python 3.12 in favour of a new statement, called `type`. So I guess we can only use it in `Shadow.pyi` and not in `Shadow.py`. It's an alias, so probably needs a different name from the `Annotated[]` argument, which is annoying.\r\n\r\nI'll try something out.",
            "created_at": "2024-09-12T09:20:54Z",
