        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Where it can be used, it might be good to support `typing.Final` as a `const` alias. It just specifies that the variable or attribute cannot be re-assigned, so it would be equivalent in the cases where it's usable. Then type checkers would complain if you reassign those variables. One snag is that you're allowed to do `x: Final = 3`, where the checker is then going to infer the appropriate type. Not sure if Cython should use `object` there, or try to pick some more optimal type?",
            "created_at": "2024-09-17T20:47:27Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/5728#issuecomment-2356902071",
            "id": 2356902071,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/cython/cython/issues/5728",
            "node_id": "IC_kwDOABDGAc6Me3i3",
