        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": ">  One snag is that you're allowed to do `x: Final = 3`, where the checker is then going to infer the appropriate type\r\n\r\nI don't think that'd work in most places unfortunately, just because cython would typically try to generate the C code\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst type x;\r\n// ...\r\nx = 3\r\n```\r\n\r\nnon-pointer `const` really only works for function arguments.\r\n\r\nThat suggests to me we shouldn't do it for now, because it'd break a bunch of valid Python code.",
            "created_at": "2024-09-17T20:52:29Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/5728#issuecomment-2356912233",
